The paper deals with the computation of the capacity of codes that avoid forbidden difference patterns, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the analysis of inequalities and algorithms for computing the capacity, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of extremal norms, which is a concept in graph theory and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS, cs.CG).
